Crosshair Assistant - Crosshair Aim Privacy Policy

Scope
This Privacy Policy applies to Crosshair Assistant - Crosshair Genie features on iPhone and iPad, including crosshair management, pro player crosshair library, training records, reaction training, recoil practice, sensitivity calculation, membership subscriptions, and feedback. This app is positioned as a professional training tool and does not provide cheats, hacks, game-rule bypasses, or unfair-play features.

Information We Store
The app stores data you create or generate locally on your device, including crosshair favorites, recent usage, training records, reaction results, recoil metrics, sensitivity conversion history, language preferences, membership status, and feedback type, contact, and content submitted in the feedback form. The current version does not actively collect ID documents, contacts, precise location, photos, microphone, or camera data.

Local Storage
Most data is stored locally on your device using UserDefaults and similar local storage. It is used to restore page state, show training trends, record favorites, and determine VIP feature availability. Uninstalling the app, clearing app data, changing devices, or system cleanup may delete local data. Unless you submit feedback or Apple subscription flows require it, the app does not upload local training data to our own servers.

Subscription and Transaction Information
Yearly and weekly subscriptions are processed through Apple StoreKit and the App Store. We read subscription products, transaction verification results, and current entitlements returned by Apple to determine VIP access. Actual payment details, card information, refunds, billing, and Apple ID subscription management are handled by Apple. We cannot access your full payment credentials.

Feedback Information
When you submit feedback, the feedback type, contact information, and content are used to diagnose issues, improve features, and handle subscription-related questions. Please do not submit passwords, ID numbers, card numbers, game account credentials, or other highly sensitive information.

How We Use Information
We use the information above to provide crosshair display, pro player favorites, training statistics, trend charts, VIP entitlement checks, subscription restoration, language display, troubleshooting, and product improvements. We do not use local training data for ad profiling and do not sell your personal information.

Third-Party Services
This app uses Apple StoreKit to process subscription purchases, free trials, auto-renewal, and restore purchases. Subscription data is also subject to Apple’s privacy policy, App Store terms, and Apple ID settings. Pro player crosshair data and previews shown in the app are for training reference only and do not imply official partnership with players, teams, or game publishers.

Data Deletion and Management
You can delete training records, remove favorites, or modify local data inside the app. You can also uninstall the app to clear locally stored data. Subscription cancellation, refunds, and renewal management must be handled in Apple ID subscription settings.

Children’s Privacy
This app is intended for general FPS training users and is not specifically directed at children. If you are a minor, use subscription and feedback features with consent and guidance from a guardian.

Policy Updates
We may update this Privacy Policy due to feature changes, subscription changes, or legal requirements. Continued use after updates means you understand and accept the updated content.

Contact Us
If you have questions about privacy, data processing, feedback, or subscription status, contact us through the App Store page or app support channel.
